# AI Development Guidelines

## Project Overview

This is a Next.js 16 florist landing page project using React 19, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS 4. The project uses shadcn/ui components and follows strict architectural principles.

## Core Technologies

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **UI Library**: React 19
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **Components**: shadcn/ui (New York style)
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Fonts**: Geist Sans & Geist Mono

## shadcn/ui Usage

### MCP Integration

- **ALWAYS** use the shadcn MCP tools when adding or modifying components
- Before adding components, check available registries using `mcp_shadcn_get_project_registries`
- Search for components using `mcp_shadcn_search_items_in_registries`
- View component details with `mcp_shadcn_view_items_in_registries`
- Get usage examples with `mcp_shadcn_get_item_examples_from_registries`
- Use `mcp_shadcn_get_add_command_for_items` to get the correct CLI command
- Run audit checklist after component changes with `mcp_shadcn_get_audit_checklist`

### Component Guidelines

- Components live in `components/ui/` directory
- Use shadcn CLI to add components, never manually copy-paste
- Extend shadcn components by importing from `@/components/ui` and wrapping/combining them
- Maintain consistent styling with existing shadcn theme (New York style, neutral base color)

## Architecture & Separation of Concerns

### Directory Structure

```
app/              # Next.js App Router pages and layouts
components/       # Reusable React components
  ui/            # shadcn/ui components (auto-generated)
lib/             # Utility functions and helpers
hooks/           # Custom React hooks (if needed)
public/          # Static assets
```

### Component Hierarchy

- **Pages** (`app/page.tsx`): Route handlers and page-level logic
- **Layouts** (`app/layout.tsx`): Shared layout structure
- **Feature Components** (`components/`): Domain-specific components
- **UI Components** (`components/ui/`): shadcn base components
- **Utilities** (`lib/utils.ts`): Pure functions, helpers

### Rules

- Pages should only handle routing and data fetching
- Business logic belongs in components or custom hooks
- Pure utility functions go in `lib/` directory
- UI components are reusable and composable
- No direct DOM manipulation - use React patterns
- Keep components small and focused (< 200 lines when possible)

## Best Practices

### TypeScript

- Use strict type checking
- Define proper interfaces/types for all props
- Avoid `any` - use `unknown` if type is truly unknown
- Use type inference where appropriate
- Export types alongside components when reusable

### React & Next.js

- Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed (`"use client"`)
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Leverage Next.js metadata API for SEO
- Use proper loading and error states
- Implement proper accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)

### Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes - avoid custom CSS when possible
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS variables for theme colors (already configured)
- Maintain consistent spacing scale
- Support dark mode (use `dark:` prefix)

### Code Quality

- Write self-documenting code with clear naming
- Keep functions pure when possible
- Extract magic numbers/strings to constants
- Use ESLint (configured with Next.js config)
- Format code consistently (use Prettier if configured)

### Performance

- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Use dynamic imports for large components
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Minimize bundle size
- Use React.memo for expensive components when appropriate

## File Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (`Button.tsx`, `HeroSection.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (`utils.ts`, `formatPrice.ts`)
- Pages: lowercase (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useCart.ts`)

## Path Aliases

- `@/components` → `components/`
- `@/lib` → `lib/`
- `@/hooks` → `hooks/`
- `@/ui` → `components/ui/`

## Additional Guidelines

- Always check existing code before creating new patterns
- Reuse existing utilities and components
- Follow the existing code style and patterns
- Test responsive behavior on mobile, tablet, desktop
- Ensure accessibility (keyboard navigation, screen readers)
- Maintain consistent design system (colors, spacing, typography)
